#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid "Save Nairobi National Park"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:60
msgid "08 JUN | Nairobi, Kenya"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:62
msgid ""
"Nairobi National Park is under threat. The park is a rare haven for wildlife "
"in a busy city; the world’s only natural wildlife park in the midst of a "
"capital. It is home to Kenya’s only black rhino sanctuary, as well as lions, "
"buffalos and over 400 bird species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:64
msgid ""
"The park also functions as an important carbon sink helping to purify the "
"air in a city where air pollution costs many lives."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:66
msgid ""
"![Lions in Narobi national park surrounded by encroaching "
"city](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTERIMAGE3.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:68
msgid "Photo: African Sustainability Network"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:70
msgid ""
"Part of a vital migration route to plains beyond it, the park was once a "
"channel for the mass migrations of zebras, wildebeests and giraffes. But "
"with the development of oil pipelines, railways, roads and extensive "
"fencing, the number and variety of wild species populating the park has "
"fallen drastically."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:72
msgid ""
"The park is now threatened by further developments, including a luxury "
"tourist resort in rhino breeding grounds and a plan to fully enclose the "
"park. These proposals contradict the 2030 National Wildlife Strategy "
"recently adopted by the government which aims to sustain natural habitats "
"and reduce biodiversity loss."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:74
msgid ""
"![Rebels calling for the development on Nairobi National Park to be "
"stopped](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTERIMAGE4.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:76
msgid ""
"A founder of the [African Sustainability "
"Network](https://africansustainabilitynetwork.org/programs/) and fierce "
"defender of the park explained: “Utter destruction will occur if this goes "
"ahead, converting the park into nothing more than a glorified "
"zoo... Ancestral lands and wildlife diversity will be diminished through "
"inbreeding, territorial reduction, culling and habitat encroachment”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:78
msgid ""
"These developments must be stopped. Watch [this "
"video](https://twitter.com/XRebellionUK/status/1271321482291851266), [sign "
"the "
"petition](https://www.change.org/p/cabinet-secretary-of-tourism-and-wildlife-najib-balala-save-nairobi-national-park), "
"support their [legal crowdfunder "
"here](https://www.gofundme.com/f/save-nairobi-national-park?utm_source=customer&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=p_cf+share-flow-1) "
"and [follow XR Youth Kenya here](https://www.instagram.com/xr_youth__kenya/)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:80
msgid ""
"Also, read [XR Africa’s first ever newsletter "
"here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-NFI6gIvhI9Xwtg7RKjRmhZ50LdmzvmMS7cuNKbERkg/edit) "
"and [sign up to the XR Africa newsletter "
"here](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfs2JGbXpUuOz1VD3rNj4F1_gi14iiz09vLAOxFfYn9dO0W5w/viewform) "
"!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Digital Wave: Indonesian Youth Rise Up!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:86
msgid "10 - 21 MAY | Jakarta, Indonesia"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:88
msgid ""
"XR Indonesia hosted a 10-day wave of digital actions that spread awareness "
"of the climate emergency and recruited hundreds of new rebels to their "
"cause."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:90
msgid ""
"Each day a new digital ‘quest’ was launched on Instagram - a climate-related "
"challenge that included attending zoom seminars, answering questionnaires, "
"and making pieces of protest artwork. You can watch some highlights "
"[here](https://www.instagram.com/tv/CAiEr2MArLk/?igshid=1w2rxibj6q5n2)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:92
msgid ""
"The quests drew in thousands of Indonesians, with hundreds posting their "
"responses each day. Many of the new recruits are school age and are now "
"setting up a national XR Youth chapter, as well as filming their own "
"‘Heading for Extinction’ talk."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:94
msgid "![](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTERIMAGE5.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:96
msgid ""
"The digital event was launched after the government held an extraordinary "
"parliamentary session, in contravention of its own lockdown rules, to pass a "
"secretive [Coal and Mineral Mining "
"Bill](https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/05/12/house-approves-revised-mining-law-amid-outcry.html)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:98
msgid ""
"The new laws sideline environmental protections and encourage rampant "
"extractivism. Last year, mining was linked to 7 natural disasters that "
"killed dozens and displaced tens of thousands."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:100
msgid ""
"This year the country has been devastated by floods and forest fires. Yet "
"the media continues to ignore the climate crisis, and most Indonesians are "
"still not properly informed about the wider links."
msgstr ""

