msgid "58 Rebels Arrested for Defending Earth Needs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:106
msgid "30 MAY | Paris, France"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:108
msgid ""
"![Rebels in Paris, France blocking the "
"Champs-Elysees](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTERIMAGE6.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:110
msgid ""
"On May 30, 58 French rebels were arrested, bussed to a police station, and "
"fined after blocking the most iconic street in Paris, the "
"Champs-Elysees. Many more were roughly [dragged away by the "
"police](https://twitter.com/LPLdirect/status/1266688393079119872)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:112
msgid ""
"The 150 strong blockade was part of a socially-distanced action called ‘Nos "
"Besoins’ (Our Needs) highlighting the real needs of the world after the "
"pandemic, such as clean seas and an ecological society, not a return to the "
"old economic ‘abnormality’."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "A Tale of 2 Coal-Fired Power Stations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:118
msgid "31 MAY & 4 JUNE | Germany & Czech Republic"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:120
msgid ""
"While Czech rebels were celebrating the shutdown of one of Europe’s dirtiest "
"coal-fired power stations, rebels across Europe were protesting the launch "
"of a brand-new one in Germany."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:122
msgid ""
"![Rebel with an extinction rebellion flag in front of power "
"station](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTERIMAGE7.jpg)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:124
msgid ""
"On 4th June the state-owned Prunerov 1 power station near the town of Kadan, "
"north-west of Prague, was finally closed down. According to a 2007 study by "
"the World Wildlife Fund, Prunéřov was Europe’s 12th worst power station in "
"terms of its energy efficiency and CO2 "
"output.[](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carbon_dioxide)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:126
msgid ""
"Four days earlier the controversial "
"[Datteln4](https://twitter.com/hashtag/StopDatteIn4?src=hashtag_click) power "
"station near Dortmund had been started up, with its operator Uniper claiming "
"it to be among the world’s most modern and efficient coal-fired power "
"plants."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:128
msgid ""
"But as "
"[protestors](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Cs1DKyshAw&feature=youtu.be) "
"made clear, it is still burning coal and still adding to the burden of CO2 "
"in the Earth’s atmosphere. Greta Thunberg called it “a shameful day for "
"Europe”."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: 2020-06-17-newsletter-40.md:130
msgid ""
"![Rebel with fake blood on their hands](/assets/uploads/NEWSLETTER""IMAGE 8.jpg)"
